    public interface IObjectParameterVisitor<T>
    A visitor of ObjectParameters in the style of the visitor pattern. Classes implementing this interface are used to operate on an IObjectParameter when the kind of IObjectParameter is unknown at compile time.

    When passing an IObjectParameterVisitor to an IObjectParameter using the IObjectParameter.accept(IObjectParameterVisitor) method, the visitor's most suitable visit method will be called. Warning In future versions more visit methods for new types of IObjectParameter might be added. This will lead to source incompatibilities for classes directly implementing this interface. To avoid this, visitor implementations are encouraged to extend the abstract visitor class ObjectParameterVisitorAdapter.
